5826/youtube-feminist-suffragette-red-dead-redemption-ban |archivedate=November 8, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<!-- Red Dead Online -->\n\n<ref name=\"IGN RDO\">{{cite web |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2018/09/19/red-dead-online-devs-reveal-first-details |title=Red Dead Online: Devs Reveal First Details |last=Ryan |first=Jon |work=[[IGN]] |publisher=[[Ziff Davis]] |date=September 19, 2018 |accessdate=August 8, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919203235/https://www.ign.com/articles/2018/09/19/red-dead-online-devs-reveal-first-details |archivedate=September 19, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Polygon 7\">{{cite web |url=https://www.polygon.com/2018/11/27/18114287/red-dead-redemption-2-rdr2-online-beta-details |title=Red Dead Redemption 2 Online: 7 things to know about the beta |last1=Kuchera |first1=Ben |last2=McWhertor |first2=Michael |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |publisher=[[Vox Media]] |date=November 27, 2018 |accessdate=December 2, 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181127191341/https://www.polygon.com/2018/11/27/18114287/red-dead-redemption-2-rdr2-online-beta-details |archivedate=November 27, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Polygon RDO\">{{cite web |url=https://www.polygon.com/2018/11/26/18112534/red-dead-redemption-2-rdr2-online-multiplayer-beta-release-date |title=Red Dead Redemption 2 Online launches in beta on Nov. 27 |last=McWhertor |first=Michael |date=November 26, 2018 |accessdate=August 8, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181127042239/https://www.polygon.com/2018/11/26/18112534/red-dead-redemption-2-rdr2-online-multiplayer-beta-release-date |archivedate=November 27, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Sales 2018\">{{cite web |url=https://venturebeat.com/2019/02/06/red-dead-redemption-2-gallops-to-23-million-copies-in-a-quarter-stock-falls-13/ |title=Red Dead Redemption 2 sells massive 23 million copies, but Take-Two stock still falls 13% |last=Takahashi |first=Dean |publisher=[[VentureBeat]] |date=February 6, 2019 |accessdate=April 10, 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190324084634/https://venturebeat.com/2019/02/06/red-dead-redemption-2-gallops-to-23-million-copies-in-a-quarter-stock-falls-13/ |archivedate=March 24, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"USgamer RDO\">{{cite web |url=https://www.usgamer.net/articles/red-dead-online-beta-stats-rank-progress-potential-reset-rockstar-warns |title=Red Dead Online: There Are Currently No Plans to Reset Player Progression |last=McCarthy |first=Caty |work=USgamer |publisher=[[Gamer Network]] |date=December 4, 2018 |accessdate=December 4, 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181205193308/https://www.usgamer.net/articles/red-dead-online-beta-stats-rank-progress-potential-reset-rockstar-warns |archivedate=December 5, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* {{Official website}}\n\n{{Portal bar|Video games}}\n{{Red Dead Redemption}}\n\n[[Category:2018 video games]]\n[[Category:Action-adventure games]]\n[[Category:Death in fiction]]\n[[Category:Euphoria (software) games]]\n[[Category:Infectious diseases in fiction]]\n[[Category:Interactive Achievement Award winners]]\n[[Category:Motion capture in video games]]\n[[Category:Multiplayer and single-player video games]]\n[[Category:Open world video games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation 4 games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation 4 Pro enhanced games]]\n[[Category:Red Dead]]\n[[Category:Rockstar Advanced Game Engine games]]\n[[Category:Rockstar Games]]\n[[Category:Stadia games]]\n[[Category:Take-Two Interactive games]]\n[[Category:Video game prequels]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in Canada]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in India]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in the United States]]\n[[Category:Video games set in 1899]]\n[[Category:Video games set in 1907]]\n[[Category:Video games set in the Caribbean]]\n[[Category:Video games set in the United States]]\n[[Category:Video games with alternate endings]]\n[[Category:Video games with time manipulation]]\n[[Category:Western (genre) video games]]\n[[Category:Windows games]]\n[[Category:Works about atonement]]\n[[Category:Xbox One games]]\n[[Category:Xbox One X enhanced games]]\n", "name_user": "76.8.147.182", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Fixed typo)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Red_Dead_Redemption_2"}
{"title_page": "Stefan Filipovi\u0107", "text_new": "{{short description|Montenegrin singer}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n|name = Stefan Filipovi\u0107\n|image = ESC 2008 - Montenegro - Stefan Filipovic, 1st semifinal.jpg\n|caption = Stefan Filipovi\u0107 in ESC 2008\n|background = solo_singer\n|birth_name = Stefan Filipovi\u0107\n|alias = \n|birth_date = {{birth date and age|1987|1|18}}\n|birth_place = [[Titograd]], [[Montenegro]], [[Yugoslavia]]\n|origin = \n|instrument = \n|genre = [[Pop music|Pop]], [[disco]]\n|occupation = Singer\n|years_active = 1999 - present\n|label = \n|associated_acts = \n|website = \n}}\n\n'''Stefan Filipovi\u0107''' ([[Serbian Cyrillic]]: \u0421\u0442\u0435\u0444\u0430\u043d \u0424\u0438\u043b\u0438\u043f\u043e\u0432\u0438\u045b) (born January 18, 1987) is a [[Montenegro|Montenegrin]] pop singer.\n\n==Biography==\nFilipovi\u0107 was born in [[Titograd]], now [[Podgorica]], and studied in the [[Cetinje]] Music Academy. He started singing at age seven and he took part in various festivals in Montenegro and abroad. On January 27, he won [[MontenegroSong 2008]], hence gaining the right to represent [[Montenegro in the Eurovision Song Contest 2008]], that was held in [[Belgrade]], [[Serbia]]. The song performed was chosen internally by a 30-member jury appointed by [[RTCG]]. The winning song was titled \"[[Zauvijek volim te]]\" (''I love you for eternity''), and was made by a team of [[Republic of Macedonia|Macedonia]]n musicians - [[Grigor Koprov]] (author), [[Ognen Nedelkovski]] (composer) and [[Vladimir Doj\u010dinovski]] (arranger), the same trio that created the Macedonian entry in [[Eurovision Song Contest 2007|2007]] - [[Mojot Svet]]. An English version of the song was also recorded, under the title \"Never forget that I love you\". The song's demo version was presented on Saturday, March 8 and was rearranged until March 15.  Filipovi\u0107 performed the song at the first semi-final of the competition, but failed to reach the final.\n\n==Singles==\n* Zujalica (Na\u0161a Radost - kids' festival, [[Podgorica]])\n* \u0110ede Pero \u0161to je ovo ([[Na\u0161a Radost]] 1999)\n* Deca imaju pravo (UNICEF kids festival, [[Tivat]])\n* Ringeringe raja (Na\u0161a Radost)\n* Ja Mogao Bih Sve ''([[Music Festival Budva]] 2005 - 4th place & Best Debutant Award)''\n* Ne Umijem ''(Sunflower Music Festival in Zrenjanin 2005 - 3rd place & Best Debutant Award)''\n* Za Nju ''([[Evropesma]] 2006 - 4th place)''\n* \u0160e\u0107er i Vo\u0107e ''(Music Festival Budva 2006 - 2nd place)''\n* Ne Mogu Bez Tebe ''([[MontenegroSong 2007]] - 2nd place)''\n* Nebo i More ''(Music Festival Budva 2007 - 1st place)''\n* [[Zauvijek Volim Te]] / Never Forget That I Love You ''([[Eurovision Song Contest 2008]])''\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080308194926/http://www.njegoskij.org/article44.html The Njegoskij Fund Network] : \"Montenegrin public voted: Stefan Filipovic to Belgrade in May\".\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080322000936/http://www.njegoskij.org/article223.html The Njegoskij Fund Network] : \"Stefan Filipovic\u2019s Eurovision 2008 song finally revealed!\".\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080626223517/http://www.njegoskij.org/article264.html The Njegoskij Fund Network] : \"Stefan Filipovic\u2019s Eurovision 2008 song presented in English version\" (final version with lyrics).\n*[http://mmm.com.mk/Text1a.asp?id=7256&Rubrika=Vesti Grigor Koprov composing a song for Stefan (in Macedonian)]{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-ach}}\n{{succession box |\n  before=[[Stevan Faddy]]<br />with ''[['Ajde, kro\u010di]]'' |\n  title=[[Montenegro in the Eurovision Song Contest]] |\n  years=[[Eurovision Song Contest 2008|2008]]|\n  after=[[Andrea Demirovi\u0107]]<br />with ''[[Just Get Out of My Life]]'' |\n}}\n{{succession box\n| before= [[Incanto (music group)|Incanto]]\n| title=[[Pjesma Mediterana|Music Festival Budva]] winner\n| years=2007\n| after= [[Ivan \u010canovi\u0107]]\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Montenegro in the Eurovision Song Contest}}\n\n{{commonscat|Stefan Filipovi\u0107}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Filipovic, Stefan}}\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Podgorica]]\n[[Category:Montenegrin male singers]]\n[[Category:Montenegrin Eurovision Song Contest entrants]]\n[[Category:Eurovision Song Contest entrants of 2008]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Montenegrin singer}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n|name = Stefan Filipovi\u0107\n|image = ESC 2008 - Montenegro - Stefan Filipovic, 1st semifinal.jpg\n|caption = Stefan Filipovi\u0107 in ESC 2008\n|background = solo_singer\n|birth_name = Stefan Filipovi\u0107\n|alias = \n|birth_date = {{birth date and age|1987|1|18}}\n|birth_place = [[Titograd]], [[Montenegro]], [[Yugoslavia]]\n|origin = \n|instrument = \n|genre = [[Pop music|Pop]], [[disco]]\n|occupation = Singer\n|years_active = 1999 - present\n|label = \n|associated_acts = \n|website = \n}}\n\n'''Stefan Filipovi\u0107''' ([[Serbian Cyrillic]]: \u0421\u0442\u0435\u0444\u0430\u043d \u0424\u0438\u043b\u0438\u043f\u043e\u0432\u0438\u045b) (born January 18, 1987, in [[Titograd]], now [[Podgorica]]) is a [[Montenegro|Montenegrin]] pop singer.\n\n==Biography==\nHe is a student in the [[Cetinje]] Music Academy. He started singing at age seven and he took part in various festivals in Montenegro and abroad. On January 27, he won [[MontenegroSong 2008]], hence gaining the right to represent [[Montenegro in the Eurovision Song Contest 2008]], that was held in [[Belgrade]], [[Serbia]]. The song performed was chosen internally by a 30-member jury appointed by [[RTCG]]. The winning song was titled \"[[Zauvijek volim te]]\" (''I love you for eternity''), and was made by a team of [[Republic of Macedonia|Macedonia]]n musicians - [[Grigor Koprov]] (author), [[Ognen Nedelkovski]] (composer) and [[Vladimir Doj\u010dinovski]] (arranger), the same trio that created the Macedonian entry in [[Eurovision Song Contest 2007|2007]] - [[Mojot Svet]]. An English version of the song was also recorded, under the title \"Never forget that I love you\". The song's demo version was presented on Saturday, March 8 and was rearranged until March 15.  Filipovi\u0107 performed the song at the first semi-final of the competition, but failed to reach the final.\n\n==Singles==\n* Zujalica (Na\u0161a Radost - kids' festival, [[Podgorica]])\n* \u0110ede Pero \u0161to je ovo ([[Na\u0161a Radost]] 1999)\n* Deca imaju pravo (UNICEF kids festival, [[Tivat]])\n* Ringeringe raja (Na\u0161a Radost)\n* Ja Mogao Bih Sve ''([[Music Festival Budva]] 2005 - 4th place & Best Debutant Award)''\n* Ne Umijem ''(Sunflower Music Festival in Zrenjanin 2005 - 3rd place & Best Debutant Award)''\n* Za Nju ''([[Evropesma]] 2006 - 4th place)''\n* \u0160e\u0107er i Vo\u0107e ''(Music Festival Budva 2006 - 2nd place)''\n* Ne Mogu Bez Tebe ''([[MontenegroSong 2007]] - 2nd place)''\n* Nebo i More ''(Music Festival Budva 2007 - 1st place)''\n* [[Zauvijek Volim Te]] / Never Forget That I Love You ''([[Eurovision Song Contest 2008]])''\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080308194926/http://www.njegoskij.org/article44.html The Njegoskij Fund Network] : \"Montenegrin public voted: Stefan Filipovic to Belgrade in May\".\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080322000936/http://www.njegoskij.org/article223.html The Njegoskij Fund Network] : \"Stefan Filipovic\u2019s Eurovision 2008 song finally revealed!\".\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080626223517/http://www.njegoskij.org/article264.html The Njegoskij Fund Network] : \"Stefan Filipovic\u2019s Eurovision 2008 song presented in English version\" (final version with lyrics).\n*[http://mmm.com.mk/Text1a.asp?id=7256&Rubrika=Vesti Grigor Koprov composing a song for Stefan (in Macedonian)]{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-ach}}\n{{succession box |\n  before=[[Stevan 